        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our target sensitivity is determined by running our worst-case (weakest signal i.e. lowest carbon abundance) models through the CASA ALMA simulator (simobserve, uvcontsub, simanalyze), and aiming for a signal to noise of 3 on the resulting spectral line intensity. This results in a sensitivity request of 10 mJy/beam.

The models mentioned above match our own single-dish measurements of CO, as well as literature data on O, C+ and HD.

The source is extended by up to ~200 AU (4'') radii, however recent studies show that a large part of the mass may be confined within 2'' radii. As our main observational goal is to measure the [CI] line flux, a resolution of ~1'' offers a good tradeoff between avoiding loss of resolved-out flux and some amount of spatial resolution on the disk.

The linewidth in this source is typically ~1 km/s. Our requested spectral resolution of 0.595 km/s is sufficient to measure the flux of such lines and to do v_lsr determination at the &lt;0.5 km/s level (depending on the detection strength).</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
